The Anchor Element: Understanding HTML Attributes

HTML Attributes
<tag attribute=value>Content</tag>
i.e.
<a href="http://www.google.com">This is a link</a>
The anchor element has a special attribute called href (an attribute for a hyperlink).


Can have as many attributes as you want, you just need to separate them with a space 
(i.e. attribute=value anotherattribute=anothervalue etc) and make sure they're all in the 
opening tag.

There are specific attributes that you can use for certain elements i.e. href only works with 
the anchor element. There are also global attributes that can be used with any element 
i.e. <a draggable="true">This text is draggable</a>